    <note>Wei(5) Qi [1941] He entered the civil service on the basis of his grandfather's yin and subsequently passed the jinshi in 1142. He served in State council in 1166-1167. Since he, or more probably his father, moved from Shouchun to Mingzhou, he is almost certainly a descendant of Wei(5) Guan [1945]. Since his grandfather held office, I am treating him as a great grandnephew of Shao [4205]. XNYL, 189.14a, 199.16b; SS, 385.5b. CBD, 5, 4233-4.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1166:  Apt. Tongzhi Shumi yuan shi1166:  Promoted to be Canzhi zhengshi concurrently Tongzhi Sumiyuan shi1166:  Promoted to be You pushi concurrently Shumi shi1167:  Dismissed from State Council to temple sinecure</note>
